headline: Tradr to Launch Leveraged ETFs on AUR, CELH, LYFT, NET & OKTA
summary: Tradr ETFs, a provider of ETFs designed for sophisticated investors and professional traders, announced that it expects to launch five new single stock leveraged ETFs on Wednesday, October 8. The funds will be listed on Cboe and all five represent first-to-market strategies. Each ETF aims to deliver twice (200%) the daily performance of its specific underlying stock.
